OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Peter
OL,4,CLovett
OL,6,F"I once thought being in a pillbox was
OL,7,Fa good idea, but I saw the result of a
OL,8,Ftank firing at a pillbox. You didn't
OL,9,Fstand much chance."
OL,11,FBeach groups were the only troops
OL,12,Fallowed to remain on the beach. They
OL,13,Fwere vital in organising men and
OL,14,Fsecuring beach positions in the early
OL,15,Fstages of the landings.
OL,17,FMr Lovett said: "We had learned to lay
OL,18,Fmatting. You are on the beach to guide
OL,19,Fvehicles off to their exits. Not
OL,20,Feverybody landed on the correct beach.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/8
